notes.body: Hello Kulbhushan,      Greetings from PharmEasy!     With regards to your order #655933901425332224-58009, we would like to inform you that the requested quantities of the medicines METHIMERCAZOLE 5 mg (4 strips of 30 tablets) and METHIMERCAZOLE 10 mg (3 strips of 30 tablets) were partially unavailable with our partner retailer.     Therefore, we have delivered 1 strip of METHIMERCAZOLE 5 mg and 2 strips of METHIMERCAZOLE 10 mg, and the remaining quantities have now been delivered accordingly.     I assure you that this change in your order has occurred only if the partner retailer has exhausted all possible alternatives to source the unavailable medicine.      ​I request you to place a new order after 7 days for the required medicine. Our retailer restocks the medicines every 7 days. If the medicine is still unavailable, I would request that you reach out to us. We will highlight your concern to the partner retailer.     For any further assistance, please reach out to us through our support channels in the App or website listed in the 'Need Help' section.     Thank you for choosing PharmEasy. Stay Healthy.     Regards,  Sandhya Nackwal

With regards to your order #655933901425332224-58009, we would like to inform you that the requested quantities of the medicines METHIMERCAZOLE 5 mg (4 strips of 30 tablets) and METHIMERCAZOLE 10 mg (3 strips of 30 tablets) were partially unavailable with our partner retailer.

Therefore, we have delivered 1 strip of METHIMERCAZOLE 5 mg and 2 strips of METHIMERCAZOLE 10 mg, and the remaining quantities have now been delivered accordingly.

I assure you that this change in your order has occurred only if the partner retailer has exhausted all possible alternatives to source the unavailable medicine. 

​I request you to place a new order after 7 days for the required medicine. Our retailer restocks the medicines every 7 days. If the medicine is still unavailable, I would request that you reach out to us. We will highlight your concern to the partner retailer.

helpdesk_ticket.description:
Dear Team,

I am really disappointed and frustrated as a online customer of Pharmeasy. Before using the application, I didn’t realise that companies can play around the limitations of digital platform (with no human interface) so well! Your company is clearly propagating the principle of customer/buyer beware, we might scam you in the disguise of online platforms.


I have placed 3 orders in the recent past and all the 3 orders have been modified by the company without intimation. And in 2 out of the 3 orders placed, they have modified the order and pharmeasy tablets without intimation; thereby charging additional money. In such instances the company fools customer by stating that the initially ordered tablets are out of stock and add their own-manufactured tablets and loot customers without informing them of such modifications. 

When I tried reaching support, the chat box is useful and will take you to agent for support over call. When you try to speak to agent, the system will tell you that you haven’t placed any order in the recent past. 

As a customer and as a appreciator of the digitalisation of economy, I am very disappointed and feel that such scams should be exposed out. 


Regards, 
9780107767/8146279547



--
